                <h1>Quick Guide to Mohawk Background Marker Touch Up</h1>
                <p>To touch up your Mohawk background marker, start by cleaning the surface to ensure proper adhesion. Once dry, gently shake the marker and apply it to any areas needing color. For an even finish, use multiple light coats instead of one heavy layer. Allow adequate drying time before handling the surface to ensure durability.</p>
